  "prompt": "What is the meaning of pay band 5200-20200 in india? What is the monthly emoluments?",
  "response": "In India, Pay Band 5200-20200 is a salary scale used primarily in government jobs and public sector organizations. Here's a breakdown:\n\nPay Band Details:\n- Grade Pay Range: 5200-20200\n- This is part of the 6th Pay Commission recommendations\n- Typically applies to entry-level and junior level positions\n- Common in government departments, universities, and public sector undertakings\n\nMonthly Emoluments Breakdown:\n1. Basic Pay: Between 5200-20200\n2. Grade Pay: Usually ranges from Rs. 1800 to Rs. 4200\n3. Dearness Allowance (DA)\n4. House Rent Allowance (HRA)\n5. Other allowances\n\nApproximate Monthly Total:\n- Basic salary + Grade Pay: Around Rs. 15,000-25,000\n- With allowances: Can range from Rs. 25,000-35,000\n\nNote: The exact amount depends on:\n- Specific grade pay\n- Department/organization\n- Location\n- Years of service\n- Individual position\n\nThe 7th Pay Commission has since introduced revised pay matrices, but many organizations still reference the 6th Pay Commission scales.",
